352→      - File List includes every new/modified/deleted file (relative paths)\n   353→      - Dev Agent Record contains implementation notes\n   354→      - Change Log includes summary of changes\n   355→      - Only permitted story sections were modified\n   356→    </action>\n   357→\n   358→    <!-- Mark story ready for review - sprint status conditional -->\n   359→    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists AND {{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   360→      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n   361→      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n   362→      <action>Verify current status is \"in-progress\" (expected previous state)</action>\n   363→      <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"review\"</action>\n   364→      <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure including STATUS DEFINITIONS</action>\n   365→      <output>✅ Story status updated to \"review\" in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n   366→    </check>\n   367→\n   368→    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist OR {{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n   369→      <output>ℹ️ Story status updated to \"review\" in story file (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n   370→    </check>\n   371→\n   372→    <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n   373→      <output>⚠️ Story file updated, but sprint-status update failed: {{story_key}} not found\n   374→\n   375→        Story status is set to \"review\" in file, but sprint-status.yaml may be out of sync.\n   376→      </output>\n   377→    </check>\n   378→\n   379→    <!-- Final validation gates -->\n   380→    <action if=\"any task is incomplete\">HALT - Complete remaining tasks before marking ready for review</action>\n   381→    <action if=\"regression failures exist\">HALT - Fix regression issues before completing</action>\n   382→    <action if=\"File List is incomplete\">HALT - Update File List with all changed files</action>\n   383→    <action if=\"definition-of-done validation fails\">HALT - Address DoD failures before completing</action>\n   384→  </step>\n   385→\n   386→  <step n=\"10\" goal=\"Completion communication and user support\">\n   387→    <action>Execute the enhanced definition-of-done checklist using the validation framework</action>\n   388→    <action>Prepare a concise summary in Dev Agent Record → Completion Notes</action>\n   389→\n   390→    <action>Communicate to {user_name} that story implementation is complete and ready for review</action>\n   391→    <action>Summarize key accomplishments: story ID, story key, title, key changes made, tests added, files modified</action>\n   392→    <action>Provide the story file path and current status (now \"review\")</action>\n   393→\n   394→    <action>Based on {user_skill_level}, ask if user needs any explanations about:\n   395→      - What was implemented and how it works\n   396→      - Why certain technical decisions were made\n   397→      - How to test or verify the changes\n   398→      - Any patterns, libraries, or approaches used\n   399→      - Anything else they'd like clarified\n   400→    </action>\n   401→\n   402→    <check if=\"user asks for explanations\">\n   403→      <action>Provide clear, contextual explanations tailored to {user_skill_level}</action>\n   404→      <action>Use examples and references to specific code when helpful</action>\n   405→    </check>\n   406→\n   407→    <action>Once explanations are complete (or user indicates no questions), suggest logical next steps</action>\n   408→    <action>Recommended next steps (flexible based on project setup):\n   409→      - Review the implemented story and test the changes\n   410→      - Verify all acceptance criteria are met\n   411→      - Ensure deployment readiness if applicable\n   412→      - Run `code-review` workflow for peer review\n   413→      - Optional: If Test Architect module installed, run `/bmad:tea:automate` to expand