{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VeEUunnEmVf2MqGECYaAtt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→description: Verify a story's acceptance criteria with real-world evidence and produce a Showboat proof document.\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→# Harness Verify\n     6→\n     7→Verify a story by producing a showboat proof document with executable, reproducible evidence. Verification includes running tests, checking outputs, and fixing any issues found.\n     8→\n     9→## Step 1: Identify Story\n    10→\n    11→If a story ID is provided as argument, use it. Otherwise:\n    12→\n    13→1. Check the current exec-plan in `docs/exec-plans/active/` for the story in progress\n    14→2. Check `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml` for the first story at `verified` status\n    15→3. Ask the user: \"Which story should I verify?\"\n    16→\n    17→## Step 2: Pre-verification — Run Tests\n    18→\n    19→Before spawning the verifier, confirm tests pass in the current session:\n    20→\n    21→```bash\n    22→npm run test:unit 2>&1\n    23→```\n    24→\n    25→If tests fail, **fix the failures first** — do not proceed to verification with broken tests. This ensures the verifier starts from a known-good state.\n    26→\n    27→After tests pass:\n    28→```bash\n    29→codeharness coverage 2>&1\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→This updates `session_flags.tests_passed` and `session_flags.coverage_met` in state, which are preconditions for `codeharness verify`.\n    33→\n    34→## Step 3: Spawn Verifier Subagent\n    35→\n    36→Launch the `codeharness:verifier` subagent with full context:\n    37→\n    38→```\n    39→Use the Agent tool with:\n    40→  subagent_type: \"codeharness:verifier\"\n    41→  prompt: \"Verify story {story_id}.\n    42→\n    43→Story file: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/{story_id}.md\n    44→Proof output: verification/{story_id}-proof.md\n    45→\n    46→Read the story file, extract all acceptance criteria, and produce a showboat proof document.\n    47→\n    48→You MUST:\n    49→1. Run `showboat init` to create the proof document\n    50→2. Run tests via `showboat exec` and capture output as evidence\n    51→3. For each AC, run real commands via `showboat exec` to prove the AC is met\n    52→4. If ANY verification step fails — fix the issue (code, tests, config), then re-capture\n    53→5. Run a final `showboat verify` to confirm reproducibility\n    54→6. If showboat verify fails, investigate and fix the non-reproducible step\n    55→\n    56→Do NOT write markdown by hand — use showboat CLI exclusively.\n    57→Do NOT skip tests — they are mandatory evidence.\n    58→Do NOT proceed autonomously without fixing failures.\"\n    59→```\n    60→\n    61→## Step 4: Verify Showboat Output\n    62→\n    63→After the verifier completes, confirm the proof document exists and is valid:\n    64→\n    65→```bash\n    66→showboat verify verification/{story_id}-proof.md\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→If showboat verify fails:\n    70→1. Read the diff output to identify which step is non-reproducible\n    71→2. Fix the underlying issue (flaky test, timing-dependent output, etc.)\n    72→3. Re-run `showboat verify`\n    73→4. If it still fails after 3 attempts, report FAIL\n    74→\n    75→## Step 5: Run CLI Verify\n    76→\n    77→Once showboat verification passes, run the CLI command to update state:\n    78→\n    79→```bash\n    80→codeharness verify --story {story_id}\n    81→```\n    82→\n    83→This:\n    84→- Checks preconditions (tests_passed, coverage_met)\n    85→- Updates `session_flags.verification_run: true`\n    86→- Appends to `verification_log`\n    87→- Closes beads issue if applicable\n    88→- Moves exec-plan to completed\n    89→\n    90→## Step 6: Report\n    91→\n    92→If all ACs pass and showboat verify passes:\n    93→```\n    94→[OK] Verification passed: {story_id} ({pass_count}/{total_ac} ACs)\n    95→[OK] Showboat verify: reproducible\n    96→[OK] Tests: passing\n    97→\n    98→→ Story ready for completion\n    99→```\n   100→\n   101→If any AC fails after fix attempts:\n   102→```\n   103→[FAIL] Verification failed: {story_id} ({pass_count}/{total_ac} ACs)\n   104→\n   105→Failed ACs:\n   106→- AC{N}: {description} — {failure reason}\n   107→- Fixes attempted: {list of changes made}\n   108→\n   109→→ Fix the failing criteria and re-run /harness-verify\n   110→```\n   111→\n   112→## Step 7: Handle Verification-Driven Fixes\n   113→\n   114→If the verifier made code changes to fix issues found during verification:\n   115→\n   116→1. Re-run the full test suite to confirm fixes don't break anything\n   117→2. Rebuild if needed: `npm run build`\n   118→3. The fixes are legitimate — they were discovered through real verification\n   119→4. Do NOT revert them. They represent real bugs caught by the verification process.\n   120→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KNQnUKBFtzFzrosUg6K7qd","session_id":"7d2c764f-deb1-4354-ad31-e0a846d19ae3","uuid":"55c82de8-7d71-455f-8fa4-d81a068460e2","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:16:59.193Z"}
