{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KNQnUKBFtzFzrosUg6K7qd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 3741 tests pass, 143 test files, 0 failures.\n\n---\n\nStory 14-7 is complete and marked for review.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n**Fix 1 (AC1) — Story file status parsing:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/sync/story-files.ts` — Updated `readStoryFileStatus()` regex from `/^Status:\\s*(.+)$/m` to `/^#{0,2}\\s*Status:\\s*(.+)$/m` and `updateStoryFileStatus()` similarly with a capture group `(#{0,2}\\s*)` to preserve the original prefix.\n\n**Fix 2 (AC2) — Beads CLI not installed:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/beads.ts` — Added `BeadsNotInstalledError` class and `isBeadsCLIInstalled()` function.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/sync.ts` — Added early check; prints `[INFO] beads CLI not installed -- skipping` and exits 0.\n\n**Fix 3 (AC3) — Session flags for Rust tests:**\n- The coverage pipeline already handles all stacks (Node.js, Python, Rust). Added explicit test proving `updateCoverageState` sets `tests_passed = true` for Rust stack.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/coverage/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` — New test case.\n\n**Fix 4 (AC4) — Ralph timeout story tracking:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/ralph/ralph.sh` — `get_current_task()` now reads the first in-progress/ready-for-dev story from `sprint-state.json` via jq. `update_status()` now includes a `story` field in the JSON output.\n\n**Fix 5 (AC5) — Proof format documentation:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/commands/harness-verify.md` — Added \"Expected Proof Document Format\" section.\n\n**Test files updated:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/sync/__tests__/beads-sync.test.ts` — 3 new tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/beads.test.ts` — 4 new tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/sync.test.ts` — 1 new test + mock update\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/coverage/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` — 1 new test\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **AC3 spec mismatch:** The story said \"The flag-setting logic only triggers for `npm test` results\" but investigation showed the coverage pipeline (`detectCoverageTool` + `parseTestCounts` + `evaluateCoverage`) already handles Rust, Python, and Node.js correctly. No production code change was needed — only an explicit test was added to prove it works. The original bug may have been observed when running `cargo test` directly (not via `codeharness coverage`) which would not update session flags, but that's by design — only `codeharness coverage` updates state.\n- **Fix 4 (ralph.sh) not unit-testable:** The `ralph.sh` changes (bash) are not covered by vitest. They would need BATS integration tests. I did not add BATS tests because the story didn't list them in scope and the existing BATS tests don't cover `get_current_task()` or `update_status()`.\n- **`isBeadsCLIInstalled()` uses `which`:** This works on macOS/Linux but not on Windows. Since codeharness targets Unix-like systems, this is acceptable.\n- **`get_current_task()` depends on jq:** If jq is not installed, the function silently returns empty string, falling back to `unknown`. This matches the previous behavior."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8ba750f79693b973 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8ba750f79693b973' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 134739\ntool_uses: 111\nduration_ms: 651315</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7d2c764f-deb1-4354-ad31-e0a846d19ae3","uuid":"6a5f980e-3ab5-4fa1-b3f2-d8172f778ff1","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:27:25.523Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do 